library(tidyverse)
data(msleep)
library(infer)
view(msleep)

Jabberwockies sleep for around 7 hours a night, on average. Perform an appropriate statistical test to determine whether the mean sleep_total in the sampled population of animal types differs from the typical value for jabberwockies.

Null hypothesis: The mean sleep_total of sampled animal types does not differ from the mean sleep value of jabberwockies. H(0): μ(sleep_total) = 7

Alternative hypothesis: The mean sleep_total of sampled animals types differs from the mean sleep value of jabberwockies. H(a): μ(sleep_total) != 7

α = 0.05

observed_stat <- msleep %>%
  summarise(mean_sleep = mean(sleep_total))
observed_stat
msleep %>%
ggplot(aes(x = sleep_total)) +
geom_histogram(bins = 30)

msleep %>%
ggplot(aes(y = sleep_total)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  coord_flip()

NA
null_distribution <- msleep %>%
  specify(response = sleep_total) %>%
  hypothesize(null = "point", mu = 7) %>%
  generate(reps = 10000, type = "bootstrap") %>%
  calculate(stat = "mean")

null_distribution
null_distribution %>%
  visualise(bins = 30)

null_distribution %>%
  visualise(bins = 30) +
  shade_p_value(obs_stat = observed_stat, direction = "both")

p_value <- null_distribution %>%
  get_p_value(obs_stat = observed_stat, direction = "both")
p_value

Reject the null hypothesis.

Perform an appropriate statistical test to determine whether omnivores sleep for significantly longer than herbivores, on average.

msleep_tidy <- msleep %>%
  drop_na()
msleep_tidy
omni_vs_herbi <- msleep_tidy %>%
  mutate(omni_herbi = case_when(vore == "omni" ~ "omni",
                                vore == "herbi" ~ "herbi")) %>%
  select(omni_herbi, sleep_total) %>%
drop_na()
omni_vs_herbi
NA

null hypothesis: Omnivores do not sleep longer than herbivores. H(0): μ(sleep)omni - μ(sleep)herbi = 0

alternative hypothesis: Omnivores sleep longer than herbivores H(a): μ(sleep)omni - μ(sleep)herbi > 0

α = 0.05

omni_vs_herbi %>%
  group_by(omni_herbi) %>%
  summarise(n = n())
omni_vs_herbi %>%
  ggplot(aes(y = sleep_total, x = omni_herbi)) +
  geom_boxplot()

null_distribution_oh <- omni_vs_herbi %>%
  specify(sleep_total ~ omni_herbi) %>%
  hypothesize(null = "independence") %>%
  generate(reps = 10000, type = "permute") %>% 
  calculate(stat = "diff in means", order = c("omni", "herbi"))
head(null_distribution_oh)
observed_stat <- omni_vs_herbi %>% 
  specify(sleep_total ~ omni_herbi) %>%
  calculate(stat = "diff in means", order = c("omni", "herbi"))
  
observed_stat
null_distribution_oh %>%
  visualise() +
  shade_p_value(obs_stat = observed_stat, direction = "right")

p_value <- null_distribution_oh %>%
  get_p_value(obs_stat = observed_stat, direction = "right")

p_value

α=0.05
